## Initializes a new Git repository

There are a few ways to do this:

1. You create a repository with a README.md on the server

    ```bash
    git clone https://...
    ```

2. when you already have a repo:

    * `git init` - Initializes a new Git repository.
    * `git clone <repository-url>` - Clones a repository into a new directory.
    * `git svn clone <repository-url>` - Imports an SVN repository into a new directory.

    Then create an 'empty' git repo on the server and:

    ```bash
    git remote add origin https://...
    git push -u origin --all
    ```

